Sentencas: This work investigates the fracture behaviour of a multi-layered system typically used in solid oxide fuel cell applications, namely the lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM) and lanthanum strontium cobaltite oxide (LSCoO) films on a yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) substrate.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: The fracture is caused by excessive residual stresses during manufacture due to a large property mismatch of the layers within the system.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: The fracture modes observed are surface, channelling and interfacial cracking.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Finite element analysis is used to determine the crack driving force (energy release rate) for the surface and interfacial cracks.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: It is found that by inserting an LSM layer between the LSCoO film and the YSZ substrate, the energy release rates for all the crack types can be alleviated compared with the system with a homogeneous LSCoO film.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications

Sentencas: To reduce the crack energy release rates further, an additional LSM-LSCoO composite layer can be inserted between the LSM and LSCoO films.
Titulo: Finite element analysis of the fracture behaviour of multi-layered systems used in solid oxide fuel cell applications
